NOJA Power Switchgear manufactures and supplies globally a range of
microprocessor based, intelligent medium voltage switchgear providing;
control, measurement and communication capabilities.

We are seeking an engineer to join our development team. The successful
applicant will enjoy being part of an organization taking Australian
technology to the world.

** Experience: **

You will have a minimum of 5 years’ experience in developing a broad range of
analogue and digital hardware, and power electronics. Your experience should
include:

  * Embedded systems electronics design, implementation and testing 
  * Development of Multilayer pcb’s: using Altium 
  * Development with 32 Bit embedded microcontrollers 
  * Design and development of power electronics 
  * A high level of expertise in analogue circuit development 
  * Experience in embedded systems development with 4G and WiFi modules and GPS highly regarded 
  * Demonstrated ability to develop, supervise and analyze prototype design proving tests 

. ** Qualifications: **

You will have a degree in electrical engineering.

** Responsibility: **

You will have the maturity, focus and intensity to manage your priorities and
projects, while providing a reasonable degree of transparency and progress to
the R&D Director.

** Personal Attributes: **

You will have the ability to quickly develop product knowledge. You will be
expected to have a "team-player" attitude, while also demonstrating strong
leadership, and accountability for delivering the best design solutions in an
effective, responsible and timely manner. You will be energetic and pro-active
with a determination to successfully meet objectives.

  
